1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 5)

3
00:01:25,019 --> 00:01:26,159
Barely got any peach fuzz,

4
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,319
yet he wears blue lipstick.

5
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:29,320
Pretty flashy.

6
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:31,519
Chris likes this type.

7
00:01:33,320 --> 00:01:35,000
I heard he even drinks with the customers.

8
00:01:36,659 --> 00:01:38,179
So he's that kind of trash.

9
00:01:39,579 --> 00:01:40,679
No wonder.

10
00:01:42,380 --> 00:01:43,219
Call him over.

11
00:01:43,380 --> 00:01:43,679
Sure.

12
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:44,840
Waiter.

13
00:01:50,539 --> 00:01:51,360
The one with the blue lips.

14
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:51,880
Bring him over.

15
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:53,420
Right away.

16
00:01:54,539 --> 00:01:55,539
Pour the drinks.

17
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:08,639
I heard Blue Moon got a new cash cow.

18
00:02:09,320 --> 00:02:11,639
I came here today just to
shake some money loose for you.

19
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:15,940
Drink up.

20
00:02:18,899 --> 00:02:19,899
Oh, right. I forgot.

21
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:22,360
Drinking with you

22
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:24,320
costs money, right?

23
00:02:24,739 --> 00:02:25,739
Curly.

24
00:02:35,179 --> 00:02:36,179
Not enough?

25
00:02:36,519 --> 00:02:37,519
Curly.

26
00:02:40,039 --> 00:02:41,039
Drink.

27
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:00,300
Brother Hao.

28
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:01,260
Brother Hao.

29
00:03:01,739 --> 00:03:02,119
Brother Hao.

30
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:03,079
What's...

31
00:03:03,539 --> 00:03:04,539
What's happening here?

32
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,639
Ah Heng.

33
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,840
Don't be nervous.

34
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:09,940
I really like this kid.

35
00:03:11,179 --> 00:03:12,499
I just want to make friends with him.

36
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:13,500
But Brother Hao...

37
00:03:13,579 --> 00:03:14,579
Don't just stand there.

38
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:15,719
Keep drinking.

39
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:18,460
Ah Heng,

40
00:03:18,699 --> 00:03:19,919
go tend to your own business.

41
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:20,920
Ah Heng.

42
00:03:25,980 --> 00:03:26,980
Go.

43
00:03:28,340 --> 00:03:29,340
Okay.

44
00:03:34,340 --> 00:03:35,340
What?

45
00:03:36,159 --> 00:03:37,159
Not enough money?

46
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:41,920
Think about it.

47
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:45,059
How many songs do you have to sing,

48
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:47,239
and how many drinks do you have to take,

49
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,960
to make this much in one night?

50
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,300
Drink.

51
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,198
I thought Chris found

52
00:04:19,199 --> 00:04:20,719
someone really special.

53
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,320
Is that it?

54
00:04:25,159 --> 00:04:25,480
Boss,

55
00:04:25,679 --> 00:04:26,679
I'll drink for him.

56
00:04:38,139 --> 00:04:39,139
Look at this.

57
00:04:39,480 --> 00:04:40,719
A loyal lapdog who can drink.

58
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:42,320
Boss,

59
00:04:42,840 --> 00:04:43,619
you really shouldn't do this.

60
00:04:43,620 --> 00:04:44,780
Things could get out of hand.

61
00:04:46,659 --> 00:04:47,659
You have a point.

62
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:51,920
But I, Guan Zhenghao, am
the last person to fear trouble.

63
00:04:54,099 --> 00:04:54,440
Boss,

64
00:04:55,079 --> 00:04:56,079
there's no need for this.

65
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,260
Let's go.

66
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:12,719
They didn't follow us.

67
00:05:13,059 --> 00:05:14,059
We're safe.

68
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:18,440
Are you okay?

69
00:05:21,619 --> 00:05:21,900
How about this?

70
00:05:22,579 --> 00:05:23,579
Want to race?

71
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,200
Let's see who gets there first.

72
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,959
What's the penalty for the loser?

73
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:30,360
Granting the winner one wish.

74
00:05:32,219 --> 00:05:33,280
Then prepare to lose.

75
00:05:33,639 --> 00:05:34,639
You're on.

76
00:05:34,679 --> 00:05:34,960
Three,

77
00:05:35,599 --> 00:05:35,940
two,

78
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:37,300
one!

79
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:08,820
Go ahead.

80
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:09,900
What's your wish?

81
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:10,940
I'm exhausted.

82
00:06:12,219 --> 00:06:13,219
I'll save it.

83
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:14,320
I'll tell you next time.

84
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,519
I'm beat.

85
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:18,960
I'm heading out then.

86
00:06:19,579 --> 00:06:21,179
You can stay here and catch your breath.

87
00:06:21,860 --> 00:06:23,019
Wait for me. I can't walk.

88
00:06:27,519 --> 00:06:28,780
I'm starving after that run.

89
00:06:33,619 --> 00:06:34,619
I'm sorry.

90
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:35,840
I dragged you into this.

91
00:06:37,699 --> 00:06:38,699
Look at you, growing up.

92
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,360
You actually know how to apologize.

93
00:06:44,059 --> 00:06:45,259
Actually, it's not your fault.

94
00:06:46,019 --> 00:06:48,000
Those thugs were dead
set on causing trouble.

95
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,119
The more you resist,

96
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:50,380
the harder they push.

97
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,920
That's just how they are.

98
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:55,779
But credit where credit is due,

99
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,380
you looked really cool back there.

100
00:07:02,159 --> 00:07:03,159
How are you holding up?

101
00:07:03,699 --> 00:07:04,699
I'm fine.

102
00:07:05,699 --> 00:07:06,179
Really?

103
00:07:06,619 --> 00:07:07,619
Why would I lie to you?

104
00:07:09,139 --> 00:07:10,539
Because you lie all the time.

105
00:07:15,199 --> 00:07:16,239
But seriously,

106
00:07:16,539 --> 00:07:17,639
how did you cross them?

107
00:07:19,099 --> 00:07:20,099
I don't know.

108
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,320
Never mind then.

109
00:07:31,699 --> 00:07:32,699
Why the sigh?

110
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,639
I was just thinking...

111
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:37,920
We got through today,

112
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,280
is behind us,

113
00:07:39,900 --> 00:07:41,220
but what about the next few days?

114
00:07:47,059 --> 00:07:48,059
Don't worry.

115
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,079
It'll figure itself out.

116
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:50,320
Leave it to me.

117
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,320
Let's go.

118
00:07:54,199 --> 00:07:54,739
What do you want to eat?

119
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:55,260
Grab whatever you want.

120
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:56,340
My treat.

121
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:05,440
Here.

122
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:06,639
Have some milk.

123
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,719
You drink a lot of alcohol.

124
00:08:09,219 --> 00:08:10,339
That can take a toll on you.

125
00:08:11,159 --> 00:08:12,159
Yogurt works too.

126
00:08:12,619 --> 00:08:13,079
Anyway,

127
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:15,100
drinking this will make you feel better.

128
00:08:15,679 --> 00:08:16,919
Didn't you say you were hungry?

129
00:08:17,260 --> 00:08:18,100
I bought you a cake.

130
00:08:18,239 --> 00:08:19,239
Eat up.

131
00:08:27,979 --> 00:08:28,979
How old are you?

132
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:31,760
Thirty.

133
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,640
Is there a rule saying

134
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,260
you can't eat this past age ten?

135
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:40,920
Childish.

136
00:08:42,260 --> 00:08:43,420
This is actually pretty good.

137
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:58,260
It doesn't taste like
childhood anymore, though.

138
00:09:15,699 --> 00:09:16,699
But seriously,

139
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:18,780
what are your plans for the future?

140
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,420
Like what?

141
00:09:23,399 --> 00:09:25,279
Are you still going to
sing at Ah Heng's place?

142
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:29,080
At worst, I just won't go back.

143
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,539
I can sing anywhere.

144
00:09:31,939 --> 00:09:32,939
That might not work.

145
00:09:34,159 --> 00:09:35,219
If Ah Heng has a big mouth

146
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,699
and tells other bar owners,

147
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:38,699
what if no one hires you?

148
00:09:45,539 --> 00:09:46,539
Then what should I do?

149
00:09:49,819 --> 00:09:50,819
Don't worry.

150
00:09:52,079 --> 00:09:53,079
I'll find a way.

151
00:09:57,899 --> 00:09:58,979
What could you possibly do?

152
00:10:00,439 --> 00:10:01,439
Problems...

153
00:10:01,572 --> 00:10:02,572
always get figured out.

154
00:10:03,659 --> 00:10:04,736
Anyway, for the next few days,

155
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:05,760
stay away from Blue Moon.

156
00:10:06,460 --> 00:10:06,920
Next month,

157
00:10:07,020 --> 00:10:08,060
you can come back to work.

158
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,300
Why are you helping me?

159
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:18,536
I'm worried no one will
buy Vandacon from me.

160
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:19,260
Get lost.

161
00:10:19,479 --> 00:10:20,659
Just eat your popsicle.

162
00:10:26,399 --> 00:10:26,760
It tastes bad.

163
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:27,840
Here, take it back.

164
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:53,640
Speak.

165
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:56,560
Brother Hao,

166
00:10:57,619 --> 00:10:59,020
yesterday was a misunderstanding.

167
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:01,399
I'm Wu Shixian's brother.

168
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:03,420
Xiao Wu.

169
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,480
Even though he fought
back out of self-defense,

170
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,520
he still ended up hurting your man.

171
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:10,620
I'm here to apologize on his behalf.

172
00:11:12,239 --> 00:11:13,239
Well, well.

173
00:11:14,199 --> 00:11:16,479
Every word you say puts the blame on me.

174
00:11:17,180 --> 00:11:19,520
Your brother cracked my man's head open,

175
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,180
and now you're blaming me?

176
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:23,840
No.

177
00:11:24,220 --> 00:11:25,399
At the time,

178
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:27,920
your man's fist was already in his face,

179
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:30,039
which constitutes unlawful assault.

180
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,779
Xiao Wu only acted to stop it.

181
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,920
This action,

182
00:11:34,960 --> 00:11:35,880
legally speaking,

183
00:11:35,979 --> 00:11:37,659
is defined as self-defense.

184
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,500
But I know.

185
00:11:40,260 --> 00:11:41,460
Brother Hao is a man of honor,

186
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,600
and your men

187
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:44,680
are fiercely loyal.

188
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,000
You are reasonable,

189
00:11:47,739 --> 00:11:48,859
so you must understand this.

190
00:11:50,279 --> 00:11:52,038
You're using all these fancy words

191
00:11:52,039 --> 00:11:54,079
just to stop me from
getting to your brother, right?

192
00:11:56,260 --> 00:11:56,720
Brother Hao,

193
00:11:57,260 --> 00:11:58,260
you're a very busy man.

194
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,460
I know that.

195
00:12:00,140 --> 00:12:01,920
Picking on ordinary folks like us

196
00:12:02,579 --> 00:12:03,579
is beneath you.

197
00:12:05,479 --> 00:12:06,718
And what if I say...

198
00:12:07,479 --> 00:12:08,779
I want to pick on you anyway?

199
00:12:10,979 --> 00:12:12,380
Then, for Wu Shixian's sake,

200
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:15,840
I'll have to stand up to you.

201
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:24,159
Let's hear it.

202
00:12:24,319 --> 00:12:26,239
How exactly do you plan
to rise to the occasion?

203
00:12:28,239 --> 00:12:29,538
Brother Hao, you front for others

204
00:12:29,539 --> 00:12:31,299
and use blank contracts
to collect interest.

205
00:12:31,479 --> 00:12:32,479
I know all about it.

206
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:35,979
If word of this gets out...

207
00:12:40,399 --> 00:12:41,520
Are you saying

208
00:12:42,479 --> 00:12:43,979
you're planning to go up against me?

209
00:12:48,420 --> 00:12:49,500
You're joking, Brother Hao.

210
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:54,140
What's your background, kid?

211
00:12:55,159 --> 00:12:56,159
Nothing special.

212
00:12:56,619 --> 00:12:57,619
Just like Wu Shixian,

213
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,239
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

214
00:13:00,359 --> 00:13:01,359
If I have a choice,

215
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:02,880
of course I'd rather make a friend

216
00:13:03,539 --> 00:13:04,840
than make an enemy.

217
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,039
Besides,

218
00:13:13,079 --> 00:13:14,560
I didn't come empty-handed.

219
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,560
Curly.

220
00:13:57,939 --> 00:13:58,939
Interesting.

221
00:14:03,380 --> 00:14:04,960
How did you find this guy?

222
00:14:09,239 --> 00:14:10,799
I just happen to have some connections.

223
00:14:15,359 --> 00:14:16,359
Fine.

224
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:17,939
You can go.

225
00:14:21,359 --> 00:14:22,359
Thanks, Brother Hao.

226
00:14:42,359 --> 00:14:44,039
I finally found you.

227
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:50,260
Ah Hao,

228
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:52,560
Uncle is going to take
you to do something fun.

229
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:53,880
Sound good?

230
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:17,800
I haven't ordered yet.

231
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,100
I ordered it.

232
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,520
It's on me.

233
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,840
That's a first.

234
00:15:25,619 --> 00:15:26,819
Why are you buying me a drink?

235
00:15:27,619 --> 00:15:28,979
Because this is...

236
00:15:29,753 --> 00:15:30,760
Blue Moon's new drink.

237
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:31,960
I wanted

238
00:15:32,079 --> 00:15:34,140
to get your feedback on it.

239
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:35,880
Using me as a guinea pig?

240
00:15:41,460 --> 00:15:42,159
A bit sour.

241
00:15:42,359 --> 00:15:43,359
Not my thing.

242
00:15:49,319 --> 00:15:50,319
Just kidding.

243
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:54,079
It's better than whiskey
or Long Island iced tea.

244
00:15:57,779 --> 00:15:58,779
Brother Hao.

245
00:16:02,979 --> 00:16:03,239
Brother Hao.

246
00:16:03,479 --> 00:16:04,479
Brother Hao is here.

247
00:16:04,819 --> 00:16:05,819
Waiter!

248
00:16:07,520 --> 00:16:08,520
Here.

249
00:16:09,199 --> 00:16:10,199
Come, come, come.

250
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:12,600
Here.

251
00:16:13,180 --> 00:16:14,180
Let me pour you a drink.

252
00:16:15,119 --> 00:16:15,659
Last time,

253
00:16:15,899 --> 00:16:17,920
I couldn't bring Xiao
Wu to apologize to you.

254
00:16:18,239 --> 00:16:19,239
That was my bad.

255
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:23,760
Stand up.

256
00:16:25,279 --> 00:16:25,880
Here, Brother Hao.

257
00:16:26,020 --> 00:16:27,356
It was my fault. Let me make it up to you.

258
00:16:27,380 --> 00:16:27,819
Come on, you two.

259
00:16:27,859 --> 00:16:28,279
Before,

260
00:16:28,380 --> 00:16:29,399
we were too impulsive.

261
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,500
We were wrong.

262
00:16:32,140 --> 00:16:33,156
Please don't hold it against us.

263
00:16:33,180 --> 00:16:34,180
Please forgive us.

264
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:44,520
You startled me.

265
00:16:50,220 --> 00:16:51,220
Xiao Mo,

266
00:16:51,779 --> 00:16:53,020
you're a friend worth having.

267
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:55,879
If anything happens on
this street in the future,

268
00:16:55,880 --> 00:16:57,800
you can use my name, Guan Zhenghao.

269
00:16:58,180 --> 00:16:58,619
Understood.

270
00:16:59,039 --> 00:17:00,279
Hurry up and thank Brother Hao.

271
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,220
Thank you, Brother Hao.

272
00:17:05,739 --> 00:17:06,779
Ah, youth.

273
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:12,840
I have things to do. I'm leaving.

274
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,359
I won't stay.

275
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:16,616
Remember our agreement
for the day after tomorrow.

276
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:18,200
I'll be on time the day after tomorrow.

277
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:23,920
It's finally settled.

278
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,140
How did you settle it?

279
00:17:30,819 --> 00:17:31,819
First of all,

280
00:17:32,020 --> 00:17:33,159
you have to calm down.

281
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:34,159
People

282
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,399
can always be reasoned with.

283
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:38,760
Appeal to their emotions and reason.

284
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:39,840
And then,

285
00:17:40,020 --> 00:17:41,500
buy them a couple of bottles of wine,

286
00:17:41,699 --> 00:17:42,699
and it's done.

287
00:17:43,239 --> 00:17:44,239
Who are you kidding?

288
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:50,880
I'm going to perform.

289
00:17:51,439 --> 00:17:52,439
Wait.

290
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:55,819
What time do you finish
the day after tomorrow?

291
00:17:57,420 --> 00:17:58,420
Around

292
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,319
11:30.

293
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:01,800
Okay.

294
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,000
Go ahead.

295
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:23,600
What a coincidence.

296
00:18:24,859 --> 00:18:26,099
What are you doing hiding here?

297
00:18:26,899 --> 00:18:28,239
What do you mean hiding?

298
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:30,100
I was waiting for you here.

299
00:18:31,439 --> 00:18:32,559
Why were you waiting for me?

300
00:18:34,119 --> 00:18:35,119
To give you some candy.

301
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,560
Here.

302
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:37,840
Brother Hao gave it to me.

303
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:39,680
Is it poisoned?

304
00:18:39,880 --> 00:18:41,736
You dare to eat something
Brother Hao gave you?

305
00:18:41,760 --> 00:18:42,560
I'll test it for poison for you.

306
00:18:42,760 --> 00:18:43,760
Okay.

307
00:19:04,479 --> 00:19:05,199
This kind of candy

308
00:19:05,479 --> 00:19:06,479
isn't meant to be bitten.

309
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:18,720
Like this.

310
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:22,079
How did it light up?

311
00:19:25,920 --> 00:19:27,039
You look so silly.

312
00:19:28,420 --> 00:19:29,420
You're the silly one.

313
00:19:32,880 --> 00:19:33,880
Still, I should thank you

314
00:19:34,819 --> 00:19:36,379
for helping me deal with Guan Zhenghao.

315
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,520
Let me tell you,

316
00:19:37,645 --> 00:19:39,565
luckily no one hit any
vital spots this time.

317
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,720
If you had accidentally
hit his face or neck,

318
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:43,259
no one could have saved you.

319
00:19:46,399 --> 00:19:47,399
How about...

320
00:19:48,039 --> 00:19:49,060
I buy you dinner?

321
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:54,820
If you don't want to, never mind.

322
00:19:55,039 --> 00:19:56,039
Fine, fine, fine.

323
00:19:56,539 --> 00:19:57,539
I'll let you buy.

324
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:09,020
It's closed.

325
00:20:10,819 --> 00:20:11,819
What do we do now?

326
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:14,539
We won't find any other place open now.

327
00:20:15,859 --> 00:20:16,859
Um...

328
00:20:17,566 --> 00:20:18,926
can you cook at your place?

329
00:20:20,359 --> 00:20:21,359
My place?

330
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:23,920
If not, never mind.

331
00:20:25,239 --> 00:20:26,399
Adults shouldn't back out.

332
00:20:31,399 --> 00:20:32,399
Come on in.

333
00:20:32,479 --> 00:20:33,479
Do you have slippers?

334
00:20:34,159 --> 00:20:34,659
No.

335
00:20:35,039 --> 00:20:36,135
I don't usually have guests,

336
00:20:36,159 --> 00:20:36,739
so I didn't prepare extra.

337
00:20:37,020 --> 00:20:38,420
Just come in. No need to be formal.

338
00:20:39,899 --> 00:20:40,899
Where's the kitchen?

339
00:20:43,479 --> 00:20:44,479
Okay.

340
00:20:50,739 --> 00:20:53,119
Do you usually eat this stuff?

341
00:20:54,939 --> 00:20:56,920
I usually just order takeout,

342
00:20:57,199 --> 00:20:58,920
eat instant noodles, bread, or whatever.

343
00:20:58,979 --> 00:20:59,979
Just to get by.

344
00:21:03,340 --> 00:21:04,340
Do you have noodles?

345
00:21:05,140 --> 00:21:06,140
On the table.

346
00:21:07,079 --> 00:21:08,079
Okay.

347
00:21:08,359 --> 00:21:09,939
Go sit over there and wait a bit.

348
00:21:10,319 --> 00:21:11,439
Can you actually do this?

349
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:32,263
[He's searching "Ten Ways To Make
Eggs" and earnestly looking at the results]

350
00:21:50,772 --> 00:21:51,253
How is it?

351
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,560
Are you okay?

352
00:21:52,699 --> 00:21:53,699
Did you get burned?

353
00:21:54,380 --> 00:21:55,380
I'm sorry.

354
00:21:55,779 --> 00:21:56,779
It's nothing.

355
00:21:57,420 --> 00:21:58,079
Go wash up in the bathroom

356
00:21:58,180 --> 00:21:59,180
and change your clothes.

